There was a big war like 14-15 years before between the Nagas and the humans.  The humans wanted the island that the Nagas lived on.  Of course, the Nagas didn't want them to so they started the war.  Riven's father died in that war.  The Nagas ended up keeping their land but they never forgave the humans.  They have been plotting revenge ever since.  It so happens that a powerful spirit, imprisoned within a stone statue, hears of this.  It tells the Nagas that if they free it, it will help them get their revenge.  The only thing that can free it is blood from a dying human.  The sacrifice must be of great importance to the humans or otherwise it won't work.  The Nagas have only one chance to awaken the evil spirit, so they take the princess.<br>
